3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses computational fluid dynamics (CFD) to simulate fluid flows, which falls under the domain of computational engineering. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning techniques to learn dynamical models and control of fluid flows, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): Although the paper does not explicitly use neural networks or evolutionary algorithms, the proposed approach can be seen as a type of neural network-based modeling and control, which falls under the domain of neural and evolutionary computing.
